sentence.text: SNORD115-TAF1 and SNORD-DPM2 dysfunction introduce possible clues to the parkinsonism and increased creatinine phosphokinase in NMS, while abnormalities of SNORD115-regulation of Ral protein signal transduction suggest links to both anti-NMDAR encephalitis and the proven predisposing catatonic SHANK3 gene.
